═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
  STACK & CONVENTIONS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

LANGUAGE: Python 3.12+
TESTS: python3 -m unittest discover -s tests  (NEVER pytest — web3 conflict)
TEST COUNT: 3360+ passing — always maintain or improve
PATTERNS:
  - @dataclass for all domain objects
  - Singletons: _instance + threading.Lock() + reset() method
  - JSONL append-only for audit (never overwrite)
  - logger = logging.getLogger("core.module_name")
  - Type hints on all public methods
  - Tests in tests/test_{module}.py — inherit unittest.TestCase
  - BLAKE3 preferred, SHA256 fallback (same API everywhere)
  - Graceful offline fallback for optional services

ADDING A NEW MODULE (workflow):
  1. Read nearest core/ module for conventions
  2. @dataclass for main abstractions
  3. Persist to JSONL (logs/{module}.jsonl)
  4. Write tests in tests/test_{module}.py
  5. Run: python3 -m unittest tests.test_{module}
  6. Add exports to dof/__init__.py + __all__

